      {
        "role": "link",
        "name": "Wall Street Debates Netflix: Is the Worst Over Or Has Its Growth Stalled?"
      },
      {
        "role": "text",
        "name": "As the streaming giant embraces advertising and stabilizes its content spend at $17 billion annually, financial observers' reactions range from relief at beating low expectations to an outlier call to sell the company entirely."
